\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Could I have your name please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Harry Fellows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 And your present address?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 53 Saltburn Road, Beechdale Estate, Aspley, Nottingham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 And you are married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Your year of marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Was 1920, December the 27}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 And your year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 May the fifth 1896.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Can you remember where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I was born at number twenty-three, Kennington Road, Old Radford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Approximately four years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Then where did you move to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 We lived - we moved to the house next door, number twenty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you move again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 We - we left - after a few years we left to number 126 Salisbury Street, Old Radford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Until about when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Until about 1911 when we moved to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 111}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  Forster Street, Old Radford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How long were you there, do you remember?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 We was there until 1914, the date of me dad's death.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 That was the beginning of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 1914, my dad died in April 1914.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 You moved in that year again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, I joined - I went into lodgings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Whereabouts, where were your lodgings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 My lodgings was in the same street, a matter of about three doors away, I should say about - 115 it could have been. Very close.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Can you remember why your family were making these moves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well, the first move was ma
de because - we lived next door to some people named Saxton, and - he'd got a good job, he'd got a good job, he worked - he was a - a winder at the pit, the Woolerton pit and - their house was decorated much better than ours was so that to save the job of
 the cost of decorating as soon - when they left my mother moved next door.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Then when your father died in 1914 you went into lodgings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I went into lodgings with some people who lived in the same yard as myself, my father would - my mother died - my mother died in 1910.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Your mother had died before your father then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Yes, my mother died in 1910. And when my father died I was the oldest in the family, and - the family split up and I went to live in lodgings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I had two brothers and a sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 You were the eldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I was the oldest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Who came next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 My sister came next. She's four years younger than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Her name was Doris?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Yes, Doris Fellows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Who came next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 My brother Edward.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How long after, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Three years after. Then - Frank Stanley Fellows, and he was born two years after, 1905.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Thirty-two. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 He came from Kipton in Staffordshire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 He was a miner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 He worked on the coalface?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 He worked on the coal face.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did they call them a collier or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well the only name that I used was a collier. Was a collier then because we call 'em colliers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did he have another job before or after he was a miner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I never knew any other job that he did, except on one occasion when he was out of - when he was out of work from the pit, but always - h
e was a collier all his life practically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did he do any casual or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 None at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 He was a miner then until he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Yes, he was a miner 'til he died in 1914.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Can you remember when your father was out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Well, he was frequently what with strikes and one thing or another, he was - frequently out of work and - they - he finished at one pit and he'd start at another one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 He didn't work in one pit all his life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Not one pit all his life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 My mother would be twenty-eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 She came from Stamford. In Rutlandshire I think, in Rutland I think it is. Ah, but it is - ah, near that - aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did she have any jobs before she married your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 She was a domestic servant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did she work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I've got a recollection - that - my mother worked at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 Hollin's}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  mill. She was a silk winder - went into silk winding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 In Nottingham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 In Nottingham. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 Hollin's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  are the - you know, Vyella, they bought Vyella. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 They}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
 bought Vyella. Vyella - Vyella bought them up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 And she was a silk winder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Silk winder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did she have any part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. No part time, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did she work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 She worked after she was married, I've got a distinct recollection of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 That was when she was a silk winder?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 You don't know what sort of hours she worked do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, I couldn't tell you what kind of hours she worked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Your mother died in 1910?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 1910 - to best of my recollection.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 That's the only sort of work she had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 That's the only work, and only then for a few years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Who looked after the children while your mother was at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Well, I was put out to nurse, I've got a strict - a strong recollection of that because I lived with these people more than I lived at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 You were put out to someone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 To some other working class family, a mining family, family of co
lliers, a father and two sons, and a daughter, and I was practically brought up with them. Until I was about - I should say - eight or nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How many rooms were there in the house at Radford, the one you were in in 1911?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well - they were pretty 
much the same, they were - three bedrooms, two bedrooms on a level and the attic - and the attic - and the attic with the roof like. A parlour, a living room, and a kitchen which we called the scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did anyone else besides your parents and your brothers and sister live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Yes. During the time - up to when I - up to when my mother died or just previous to when my mother died, she had - most time two women lodgers. The - the factory which was nearest to us, the Raleigh - Raleigh Cycl
e Company - were just introducing female labour and a lot of girls were coming from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 Birmingham}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
 to work on compressors - and all such machines as that which the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 Nottingham}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
 girls had never been used to and these girls, me mother generally took two of these girls for lodging purposes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. None - not that at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Was the washing done at home or was it sent out?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 The washing was always done at home, and in addition my mother did - two differe
nt people's washing. I remember as a boy of eight - when I was eight or nine years old, fetching this washing on a Monday morning with a - little - box on wheels, a little barrow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 She did that for payment did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 She did that for payment, yes. She used to charge a penny an article.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your mother or father mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Not that I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Were they new or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 second-hand}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 My father did mend shoes, on occasions. He'd put nails in your shoes and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Were they new or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 second-hand}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  clothes when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Always new, I never remember }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 second-hand}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Where were they bought from normally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Mostly out of clubs. Like a clothing club, they used to pay so much a week and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Was there any particular time when they were bought or just as they were needed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
When - mostly my little - my - my sister, I remember she was generally rigged out for the Anniversary at the Sunday school which was in May, but - normally w
e - or us boys, we had Sunday suits but I can't remember it being bought at any particular time or for any particular occasion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 You were saying when times were hard your clothes might be pawned on a Monday and brought out on the weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 When ti
me were hard, I remember during the time - during the time of the coal strikes and things like that and - occasions like that - I can remember my - my mother packing our clothes away on a Sunday, we only had our clothes - best clothes on a Sunday and I ca
n
 remember my mother packing the clothes away on Sunday night and off to the pawn shop on Monday morning and then she'd fetch them out again on Friday night when me dad come home. She got into that way when these strikes and you never seemed to be able to 
get out of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your father help your mother with any jobs around the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 None at all. I've got no recollection, my father was very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 ,very}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  - he was not domesticated at all, he couldn't knock a nail in wall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What about dressing or undressing the children and bathing them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 My mother did all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What about reading to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No recollection - I've no recollection of my mother or - or my father reading to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Or telling stories to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. None at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your father take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
My father - during the times - especially during the times of - when he was on strike and - and out of work, always took me out - up to when I was about nine years old, he used to take me out on a Saturday,
 we used to go - blackberrying, mushrooming, bird nesting. But he used to do that to get out of the way on a Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did he look after you if your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Not that I can remember, I can't - up to the time of me mother died, after me mo
ther died he did. He used to see that we were bathed and everything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you have any jobs you had to carry out in the home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I frequently used to - on washdays which were always Monday and Tuesday, I reme
mber; my mother had the two wash - to ponch tubs on the backyard and the old fashioned mangle and the copper going in the scullery, and she used to get me to ponch. Ponch with the old - before the - you know, the - they had a wooden ponch you know in thos
e days. Did you, we used to call 'em ponches. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 And you used to take the washing to these people in a little truck?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I used to fetch it in a - in - on a Monday morning for her, she used to take two people's washing in, I fetched it on a Monday 
morning. And then I used to take it back on Friday night and bring the money in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How long did you do these sort of jobs for, until you were how old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Oh until I - she - until me mother died. Until me mother died.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What about when you left school when your were thirteen or fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I left school at thirteen. And then I went to work - I went out to work then, but before -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 That would be about the time your mother died anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Yes. Yes. Well that - I'd started work in 1909.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Your mother died in 1910 so you couldn't do any jobs around the house for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 didn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  do any jobs around the house but when I was nine years old - I went to work for a butcher on a Saturday. I went at eight o'clock in the morning 'til nine o'clock
 on Saturday night and I used to go - taking, you know, delivering orders, meat. I started when I was nine and worked - and worked for him until I actually started working full time, when I left school. He used to pay me one and six a day, for the day, gi
ve me a penny for myself and a quarter of sausage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your brothers and sister have any regular little jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Not that I know to, I can't remember my - my sister used to help me mother a bit but of course she was only very young at the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What about helping the younger children to dress and eat, did the older ones look after the younger ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Not - not to my knowledge. They - my mother used to look after us, get us off to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time when you were a schoolboy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
According to your age. According to your age, when I - when you got - being the oldest in the family you were allowed to stop up a little bit longer than - than the others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What sort of time, can you remember, what about when you were about twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Before I - just before I left school I should say it'd be somewhere - I wasn't really fixed to time then but I can remember I generally used to go off to bed about ten o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 When I was very young me mother always put me to bed, not me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 At what age did you put yourself to bed, can you remember?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Oh - oh is should say about nine. About nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you share the bedroom or the bed with anyone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
We had - I've got a recollection that - that two girls lodgers had one bedroom, we three brothers - or - my - myself and my brother slept up in the attic in a double bed. And - the babe - the youngest and my sister slept on a bed in the same ro
om as my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What room did you used to have a bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 We had no bathroom. We had a bath in the living room in a big zinc bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How often would this take place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Every Friday night. Religiously.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 When did you have a clean change of clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 After your bath. Every time you had a bath you had a clean change of clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Always in the living room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Were there any special occasions when you had a meal in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Well, it could be on occasions say like Christmas or if it was a birthday, my mother would give us a special treat by laying tea in the parlour, and that was a special treat to look forward to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Where did your mother cook normally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 She 
had a gas stove in the scullery, in the kitchen. But invariably she did her cooking on one of the old fashioned grates, where the fire in the middle, the water boiler at the side and a - and an oven at the side - at the other side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Our breakfast - was - eaten - my father - during the time of his lifetime I never remember my mother cooking my father's breakfast. Always he was away - he was up in the morning I should say somewhere about quarter past four and - he used to g
et his own breakfast ready, I never knew what he really had for his breakfast. But - we had the two girl lodgers, they got up next. They used to see themselves off. And then my mother used to get us up. And - and my mother - I can't remember my mother eat
ing a breakfast. But - she always used to look after us for - for breakfast.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 So all you children would be all together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 All together for breakfast. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What sort of breakfast did you used to have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well - mostly - bread and lard or so
mething like that. You - we could go and buy, I remember at the time buying - you could go and buy Egyptian eggs at twenty-four a shilling. And you could get a pound of bacon for sixpence, but I can never remember as a child having egg and bacon for me br
eakfast. If it was a special treat on a Sunday morning, we might get a slice of bread dipped in the fat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you have tea or cocoa or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Invariably tea. I mentioned that a butcher used to give me a penny. On a Saturday might when I was coming 
home from the butchers I used to call and get a penny packet of cocoa and that used to be my special treat on a Saturday night, I used to have this mug of cocoa.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What about midday, dinnertime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Dinnertimes we always had a good dinner. Always a hot dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Who would be at the mealtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 The two girls who were - and the three - and the children, the four children and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 The girl lodgers came home for their dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 They came home for their dinner and we had - all had dinner together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What about your dad, he was at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
My dad was at work. And when he came home he always had his dinner on his own when he - me mother used to cook a dinner specially and he had that when he got home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 And for the teatime meal it'd be all the children together then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
All the children together, we'd have our tea when we came home from school. The girl lodgers'd come in and they'd have - they would have their tea, but my father had had his dinner then. He'd come home somewhere about - half past five I should say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your mother or father bake their own bread?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
On occasion my mother baked her own bread but she used to bake a lot of - cakes and scones and things like that. She used to make a big seed cake in a - in a big dripping tin. And we used to cut a big slice out of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What about things like jam and bottled fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Jam - she - I - can't remember, she did on occasion, made jam if she got hold of some cheap fruit, she'd make jam, gooseberry jam or plum jam but - and - I know she used to do big jars of pickles, pickled onions and pickled cabbage and things like that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What about homemade wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, I can never remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Medicines - my father - always collected a lot of herbs, w
hat we used to call yarrow, stinking mammy, elderflowers. And always down the cellar what we used to call the little cellar, he used to - about - in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11889103\charrsid815340 summertime}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  he'd go and hang paper, knock nails in the wall and hang paper on the - on these nails and t
hen he'd come in on the Saturday with a bunch of - or when he was coming home from work he'd collect it, bunches of these herbs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What were they called again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 We used to call one - one was called stinking mammy, I can see it now, often - often se
e it, it's a tall flower, with a - a - a tall plant with yellow flowers, yellow flowers, and it - they used to put these into a - pot, boiling water, and stinking mammy was used for bruises and things like that. On the flash. Yarrow, he used to make yarro
w
 tea. You - cut the - the heads of the flowers when they were dried, put them in a cup, boiling water and we used to have it on the hob, and if you'd got a cold you'd have a drink of that when you went to bed, and you'd wake up in the night and think you'
d
 wet the bed with sweating. Used to sweat out of you. He was - in those days the doctors were - before the health service, before you know before the - of course when the health service came out - that altered these things because you got the doctor - you
 got the doctor that you called, but previous to that - now I remember my father - at the pit they had what they called a pit doctor and he paid either threeha'pence or tuppence a week and he got the - he got attention off the pit doctor you see. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 But for us - it was very, very seldom that he called the doctor in.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Was there any beer brewed in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Often we used to mother used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8282280\charrsid815340 brew}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  ginger beer. Used - I remember used to go and gather nettles and things like that for it, dandelions. Herb beer and ginger - we called herb beer and ginger beer.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your father or your mother grow their own vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 None at all. I've got not recollection at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did they buy any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well they bought the biggest part of them, of - of the vegetables. They had to buy the vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Can you remember tinned or dried fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 The only thing I remember as a child was - tinned salmon, on occasion, sardines and - latterly tinned tomatoes, although - tinned tom
atoes I don't think came in 'til much later on, we used to get very cheap Italian tomatoes, what we used to call plum tomatoes, they're about tuppence a pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did they keep any livestock, hens, pigs, goats and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. Nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Well - frequently really, meat for dinner, we always used to have a joint on a Sunday, I remember that. Cold - cold on a Monday. Mother used to hash it up - on a Tuesday. And then Wednesday we'd prob
ably have sausage. And then Thursday probably stew. She'd get stewing beef. But we did have - we had much more meat then than I do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What about tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Can't - never remember tinned meat. The first recollection I've got of tinned meat wa
s - bully beef during the - corned beef during the war, first war, and that was the first recollection I've got of corned beef.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you ever get any extra meat such as rabbits from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well sometime my dad'd come home - if he'd been out at
 the weekend for a drink, would sometimes come home with a rabbit. But that was the nearest - I should suspect that they'd been poached and he'd bought them - he'd bought it in the pub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Can you ever remember seeing your mother going without food or having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Yes. My father was the principle - he was the first, he'd got to have - he'd got to have the main - the main things in the family, and the children - we had really what was left.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 So you can definitely remember your mother going without?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 My mother I remember, do remember my mother going without so that we could have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 At the table were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. The discipline was very strong, I mean if we tal
ked or - anything at the table, if we refused anything, if we refused the food that was put on the table we were made to shift form - move from the table. And not allowed anything else until - we'd ate it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 So you were given your food to eat and you couldn't pick and choose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 We couldn't pick and choose. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What was your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 parent\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  attitude if you left some food on the plate uneaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well - the only thing we got a - we got a - a scolding and if we left any food my mother immediately th
ought we weren't well. We generally used to manage to eat everything that was put in front of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
If there was something on the table that you wanted like the salt would you be able to ask for it or would you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Well the salt was invariably in a - you know, the salt pot and - on the table and the paper pot, I can't remember mustard, we used to help ourselves from the - from the pot on the table. We didn't ask for it, we just helped ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, I can't remember, it used to be put out for us and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 We was always told that - taught how to hold our knife and fork and never to eat with your knife and all such things as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 And to sit up at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Oh yes. And keep your - keep your elbows off the table and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Were you allowed to bring toys or books to the table?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 None at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Not until we'd finished and then we had to ask, please my I leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 you\rquote ve}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  already told me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you always have the same place at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Always. My fa
ther sat at one corner. My mother at the other. My mother - my father on the left hand side, my mother on the right hand side near the fire and - we always sat at the same place }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 every time}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  we sat down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How was the meal served - who brought it in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Well my mother used to take the pans into the scullery when she'd cooked in - in the living room, take the pans into the scullery, serve the dinner out on a plate and bring the plates in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Was there any special order in which you were served?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I
 can't remember that, there was - no, I can't remember that there was any distinction there as I said before, it was very seldom that my father sat at the table with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your younger brothers and sister sit separately before they could feed themselves before they could sit up at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
They sat - they sat in a high chair at the side of me mother and me mother when they were too young to feed themselves my mother'd feed them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 When were they able to join in the family meals, when they were about three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Yes, as soon as they were able to, the better the - the sooner - the sooner they could do it the better my mother liked it because it was less trouble for her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Was your mother an easy person of you to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well - I could never remember - never remember having a serious talk to my mother, of course - my mother died when I was fourteen so that -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did she show affection easily or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 She was - she was rather affectionate - she was very upset if either of us we
re ill or anything like that, but I can't - I can't remember her showing any undue affection.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 If you had any worries could you share them with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well - I can't remember really having any worries. As a child - I was only young and I can't remember having any real worries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Was your father easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
He was the type of man, he used to talk to me, he used to tell me things and - he was a man with a marvellous memory and - mainly he used to talk to me on sport, I've got a recollection of that but mainly he'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8282280\charrsid815340 talk}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  to me on sport.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Was he an affectionate father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. I wouldn't say that he was affectionate. He was just simply - he was the man who earnt the money for the house. He was the breadwinner.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 If you had any worries could you go to him with them or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 From what I know I would }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 sooner}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  have gone to me mother than me father if I'd been in any trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Very respectful. Very respectful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did they bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, not that I - only as a family, I can't remember them bringing me up in any special way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did they teach you to hit back and look after yourself if you were involved with other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Oh definitely. Oh if somebody hit you it was no good going in crying. You - you know what you'd get, you'd probably get another one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be? Did they have any special sort of hopes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
None at all that I can remember, the only thing I think that my mother was thinking about was getting old enough to get out to work and earn some money to help keep the house. I can't remember her ever thinking about me being - any special occupation.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did they bring you up to consider certain things in life more important than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. They were very strict on religion, that's the only thing I can say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Never heard any - I never heard any bad language in the house. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Never at all. I mean, little pigs had got big ears and - speak when you're spoken to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What about when you did something that they considered to be wrong, what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Well my mother was - always the one who - was the disciplinarian in the house, I can never remember my father - hitting me or any of us. My mother was the disciplinarian. She had a - a - a stick, a c
ane hanging up on a - on a picture over the fireplace and she'd only got to lift her had up towards that and we knew what was coming, we used to run out of the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 So your mother was the one who exercised the discipline?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Your father never had to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
She'd threaten us with, I'll tell your dad, but - and - I have got a recollection of one of my younger brothers once - Ted, next - the next brother to me - I don't know what the occasion was but - I have got a recollection of me dad
 - going to unbuckle his pit belt but - he never used it. Just threatened him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Do you remember any special occasion when you were punished by either of your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 The only - the only thing after me mother was - after my mother died I do remem
ber on one occasion - my father complained about my hair, when I was young - my hair was very fair, more of a - going towards whiteness, and as I got older it changed colour. And he said I wasn't washing it, washing me hair properly. And he got hold of me
, I can remember now, he held me by the scruff of the neck under the tap, cold water tap, and gave my hair a thorough lathering.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Do you remember how you felt about being punished?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well, I felt no resentment. No resentment, well I think we used t
o look upon it in those days that - if we did wrong we got punished, and that was all there was to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Would you say you received the ideas you had about how to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8282280\charrsid815340 behave}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  from both of your parents or did one of them play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Well - she was the - she was the disciplinarian but I can't remember, you see, I was so young really when - when she died - the only thing I do remember, I do remember this definitely - as a boy, well my father, he was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8282280\charrsid815340 about}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  all day on Saturday drinking and I did formulate the opinion during that time that I'd never do that, I can always remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Not normally, I've - I have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 recollection}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  of a - a special - special birthday with we'd probably have tea in the front room, in the parlour as we called it. That would be a special occasion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Was it normal to receive presents on a birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you have guests to a special tea or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
No, I can never remember it. My mother used to probably have her - her mother come to see us on occasion. And - we'd probably have either me mother's sisters or - something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Can you remember anything that you did with your mother or your father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
No, it was - we used to have the usual - Christmas dinner, probably it used to be a piece of pork or - it could be a rabbit. We always had a plum pudding which our mother made herself - always used to make her o
wn plum puddings, and in - for tea always had tea in the front, in the parlour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 None at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Any of your family players?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 My - none of the family played any musical instrument, they wer
e not musical at all except my father. My father was a good singer. But - he - used to sing on occasion when he felt in the mood, but - they used to get him on I know when he used to go in the pubs, they used - did used to get him singing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 So you didn't have musical evenings together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Not - no, not that I can remember. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. I never - I can remember my - remember my mother hav
ing - books like - Jane Austen's books or - Little Women and - the Pride and Prejudice and one - I can always remember those being on - the - a shelf in the front room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What about newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 The evening paper - the local evening paper. That was all. I can't remember a Sunday paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Do you remember your father or mother reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well - she - she had these books but I can never remember - she never had time to do any reading. Never remember her reading - or me 
father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did they ever read aloud to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well I remember distinctly both my mother and father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Can you remember who attended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well, for my mother - mother's fune
ral, all her brothers and sisters, she came of rather a big family. I don't think there was any of my father's relatives there because they were all in America.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How about when your father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 When me father died it were a just a repetition of 
when me mother died. Just the family, I don't think there was any of his relatives there then. 'Cos we couldn't contact them at all, they were all in America.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did people wear special morning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. But always black. Everyone wore black. E
ven if you had a suit of clothes dyed. But everyone wore black. You would never dream of going to a funeral in those days in anything else but black. The men - the men always wore bow - bowlers. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Were you taken out visiting to neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I've got a recollection of my mother taking me to an aunt of hers at Collick, she lived at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 Collick}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  one of her father's sisters, but that's the only - thing, we - sometimes used to go down to Meadow Lane to - her brother's and his wif
e, to our uncle's. In Nottingham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 So that would be your mother taking you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Were you ever taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. Unless my mother wanted to buy me a pair of shoes - pair of boots or anything like that, or a suit - suit to fit on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 
When my father was - either out of work or on strike - he always - he'd got no money then to go out in the pubs and he always took me out on a Saturday and we used to go out in the country either black
berrying, mushrooming, birdnesting, anything to get out of the way. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 We'd take - bread and cheese, nobs of bread and cheese and probably a bottle of water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Do you remember any other outings with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I've got - only one recollection that
 one August Bank Holiday Monday, and it's the only time that I've got a recollection that I went away from Nottingham with my mother and dad, and that was - we went - one of these girls who lived with - well - all of them practically come from Birmingham,
 who lived with us, and I've got a recollection of going over to Birmingham on August Bank Holiday Monday to see this girl to this girl's brothers. And they lived - I'll tell you where they lived, on Summer Lane. In a little - I can see it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 That was on a Bank Holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you ever go away for a holiday then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
I can never remember going away for a holiday, but an old aunt of mine - told me the other week that - my mother and dad took me to Blackpool, but I should obviously be to
o young to remember that. I couldn't remember, I've got no recollection of it at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How did you spend Saturdays, if your father was home you went out with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well - ah, and other that that when I was nine I went to work. I had a job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 And Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Sunday, always Sunday school, half past ten in the morning and - I think it was before half past ten. But we used to go to Sunday school on a Sunday morning. Sunday school on Sunday afternoon. Always. We had a - star card which had to be ma
rked and shown to me mother when we came home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you have different clothes on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Always. Always had a Sunday suit and shoes and - stockings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Would you play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, I can never - oh they wouldn't have that at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your parents think it wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Oh definitely. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your parents attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. Neither of them. But they were always keen to see that we went. Me mother especially. I don't
 think me father would have bothered, my father - was more or less an atheist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What denomination was the Sunday school that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Church of England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Were there any outings from the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 We used to have the - summer - 
you know, the summer outing, either to Codnor Park or Plumtree, somewhere like that, we'd go - either go on a train or - to Plumtree and Codnor Park we'd - go on a dray - on the drays. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Horse and dray.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Were there any other activities organized by the church that you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
No - well, always Band of Hope on a Monday night. As a matter of fact I - I've got a certificate for writing an - an essay on - the effects of alcohol on the human body, that was given by the Band of Hope Union. I've sti
ll got that, that's in this Bible I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. I never belonged to the choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your church run a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well that was it, the Band of Hope, what they called the Band of Hope, and we used to me
et every Monday night when you would talk about the - you know, the - the strong drink and all this that and the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 You went to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Always, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you belong to any other club organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, we had - I remember the church opened a - a kind of a youth club, it was one of the first I ever knew and - was on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 Faraday}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
 Road, it was an old - schoolroom. Just one room and we used to - all us youths there, we used to go and we had - boxing - and things like that that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, I could never remember grace being said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Always said our prayers at night, up to a certain age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well I should say - when I should be 
about ten. But all the children, you know, when they were young, the three - younger than me, they were brought up to say their prayers - before they got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 in bed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  - mother used to see to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you ever have family prayers all together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I don't know that he took a - a big interest in politics. I do know that - his views were Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Do you know why he held those views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 More I should think from obstinacy, according
 to what I could gather from a conversation I did have with him, he told me about the people he worked with and all that and - I should say it was more from obstinacy than anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Was your mother interested in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Never heard her mention politics. I don't think women were interested in politics in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Do you remember your father voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well he - he always voted. I do know that he - both municipal and - general elections. I should imagine that he would vote Tory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
In some places at that time men felt they were risking losing their jobs or their house if they voted differently from their employers, do you know if your father felt himself under any kind of pressure to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
No, I don't think he found any pressure to vote for a particular - for any political party, but I do know that - he was a non - union man at that time and - I know there was a - just coming into the pits at that time was - if a
 man didn't belong a union he'd got to leave the pit, and I know definitely he left one pit to go to another for that reason.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Was he a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Do you remember him working for one of the political parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. none at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Or your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did they take part in any political activity other than at election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 None at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well - my father - he didn
't get home from work 'til - he was out at half past four in the morning, he didn't get home 'til half past five in the evening, when he'd had his dinner he used to get on the - on the couch and go to sleep, get up, have a wash and off to bed. At the week
end, invariably he was out all day Saturdays, I've already said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. None.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did she ever go out on her own to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, not that I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Your father would spend most of the evenings at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Occasionally on a Friday night, I can remember, when I was - quite young, about eight or nine, or even when I started working on a Saturday, my father'd take me to the Empire on - Friday night. Music hall. On a Friday night. We used to go in the gallery.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did he attend any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 He used to go in a pub on a Saturday, but no clubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your mother go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. Occasionally my mother - on occasion he'd - he'd say to her, you can come down and - come 
down to see me tonight but don't come before about half past nine, you know, on the Saturday night. And - I can remember on occasions like that were not - not very frequent, you'd think my mother was going away for a weeks holiday to see her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
He was very interested - he didn't take part in any, not from a - you know what I mean from a - a personal point of view, he didn't play football or cricket or anything like that but he was always interested in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did he attend the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I've got no recollection of him ever going to a race meeting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Was he a betting man?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, I can't - I remember as a boy once - another boy told me about a horse that was going to win a certain race and I told him 
about it and he gave me a shilling to go and put sixpence each way on it and the funny thing was this horse won at twenty-five to one. That was the only time I ever knew him having a bet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your father or mother belong to any savings club, a sick fund or for clothing or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Not that I can remember, my father paid - into a fund at the pit, he paid - they used to pay then - the colliers used to pay - what they called for the pit doctor, they paid somewhere about tuppence a week I 
think it was for medical attention from the pit doctor and they also paid into what they called a fatal accident fund. For - if they got killed in the pit or had an accident.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How did you get on with your brothers and sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Oh quite well. As brothers and sisters, there was no special - nothing special about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Was there any one of them that you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well - at the time I used to play with other boys the same age in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you play with your brothers and sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, I can't remember, I was the big boy of the family and rarely - there was so much difference between me and my next brother that -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 You played mainly in the street did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What sort of games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Well we used to play - tin lurky, kicking tins about and used to be up to all sorts of pranks. Tying cotton from a lamp post to another drainpipe to knock }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 people\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  bowler hats off when 
they're walking down the street and - tie two doors together and knock at the door and - knock at both doors. I think we used to get up to bigger pranks than they do now. Only we was less - there was less harm - more harmless about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Well I can never remember - only on a Sunday. Only on a Sunday, if we ever got dirty on a Sunday that was the time but - we was in trouble then but - in the week, no, I can never remember my mother having any restrict
ions on how we were. The only thing we got told, get under that tap, if you were dirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Could you play with anyone that you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well we were all about the same where I lived, wherever we lived we was all about the same - status, so that the
re was no real restriction on who we played with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you belong to a youth organization?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, only - only with church, used to go to Sunday school and the - the church had a bit of a youth club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you keep any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I've got a recol
lection of having a rabbit. I had - one or two rabbit, but they were - I think mainly they brought in with me dad for me to feed up ready for the pot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you collect anything, like stamps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Cigarette cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. The only thing that I can remember doing in the winter when I was a lad I had a - a fretwork saw and I used to do fretwork.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you go out fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. Never been fishing in my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Cycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I did have a bike when I started work, I bought - me dad - me dad bought me an old bike, I think he gave twelve shilling for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 But that was merely a means of getting to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Mainly - mainly as a means of getting to work.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What about walks, did you go for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 As a boy we used to go out in a gang of boys and we'd go out in the country bird-nesting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you take part in any sports yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you go out to any theatres, concerts, music halls, you went out with your father sometimes on a Friday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Anything else you can remember doing in that sort of field?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, I can't remember any - being interested any - in any amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Only given a penny that the butcher gave me, I think - me dad used to give us a penny on Friday night. Used to give us a penny each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Can you remember what sort of things you spent it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well mainly sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after the house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 When she was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 The only thing that I can remember we used to get on as best we could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What happened when one of your younger brothers or sister was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well my mot
her - always had a confinements at home and - the only thing that I can remember is - my father used to put as much time as he could in and - see that we was all right. But we never had any special help in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. The nearest that I can remember is - down near Trentbridge, one of me mothers brothers lived.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How much did they see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Oh an occasion. Just an occasion, there'd probably be - me mother's brother'd probably come 
to the house and bring his son and - on - on special invitation, they'd just come when they felt like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I wouldn't say they had friends, more acquaintances. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 
My mother did have one particular friend who lived near
 us when I - where I was born, and - I think she was the instigator of us moving out into Salisbury Street, because she lived there and it must have been through her influence that me mother went to live with - live near her. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 She was a - a real respected friend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Where did they see their friends then, in each others home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 In each others home, if my mother wanted to go and have a talk to this friend she'd go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did they share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, other than the fact that they were friends together, I can't remember 'em - any other friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 And your mother had this one special friend of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Just this one special friend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your father have any special friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, only what he met in pub, his -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Casual pub acquaintances?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Probably next door neighbour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Were friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Not any special, people used to come when they wanted, when they felt like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 Always a cup of tea, as soon as any of 'em come in the house the kettle'd be put on.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What about on particular days or occasions, can you remember anything special?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, no, I can never remember any special - so and so's coming, or anything like that. My mother's - mother, she lived up Melton }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8282280\charrsid815340 Mowbray}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
 and - she'd come to see us but there was never any notification that she was coming, she'd probably take it into her head and just walks in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Would you say the friends that did come to the house were your mother's friends or your father's friends or friends of both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Mainly me mother's I should say. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Those that did come would call in casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Just casually - yes. No special invitation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did neighbours used to pop in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 They used to just walk in one another's house and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your parents go out to visit friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, not that I can - me mother sometimes used to take us to - you know, to see her brother or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 We're told that in those days people made 
their own amusements, what did your parents do when they got together with their friends and neighbours, did they create their own amusements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. Not that I know - I can never remember - you see, there was only - we was only children and therefore -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Would they ever make music in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, no, I can never remember no - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Many people divide society }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8282280\charrsid815340 into}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  different social classes or groups don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 In that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one class and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well I did, but - mainly they were all working class but we did really class tradesman in a - in the - class above us. The }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 trades people}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 . Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 You would say you belonged to the working class?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Oh definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What sort of people belonged to your class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well just the same as us. Ordinary - just ordinary working people. Mainly miners, mainly miners. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
No, I can't remember - being - I know on occasion if we went to - to anywhere my mother'd say, now mind your manners. That was the general thing, mind your manners and don't forget you have to take your cap off when you go in the house and all 
such things as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 But you weren't taught to touch your cap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Or show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. I never remember being told that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Was there anyone you had to call sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, only the schoolteacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these sort of ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Not that I can remember, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 In your district of Radford who were considered to be the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well, I should say that the vicar - the local policeman, the doctor. And - well that'd be all as I can - as far as I can see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you come into contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Only through - going to church I come in contact with the vicar, I doubt - he knew my name and that's about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Why do you think these particular people were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Well mainly I should say from a point of view of education. Superior - superior education and therefore - could give you the answer to your problems if }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8282280\charrsid815340 you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What about shopkeepers, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 trades people}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 , who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well mainly themselves. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 clergy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  and teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well I can't remember them - - ever mixing with anyone, of course at the church and all that and Sunday school they used to come rou
nd and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you ever come in contact with any employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, I worked for - I worked for a man all me life and I don't suppose he knew what me name was. He knew me as a checkman but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What sort of people would you say went to church, to the church that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well - for my experience I should say the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 trades people}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 . My - my father used to say they used to go from a matter according to business. It wasn't religion, it was business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Was there a chapel in your district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Yes, quite - one or two chapels.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What sort of people went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well - main - working class people, just a different religion, they used to treat the religion differently and that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Where you lived did all the people in the working c
lass have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups within the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Well - there was one or - there was really one or two families who really stood out. Particularly one - one that I remember was this friend t
hat I've mentioned of my mother's. Now her husband had got a regular job at the pit, he was a - winder, at the pit, on the engine, letting the man down, up and down the pit shaft, and he always had a regular job. They'd had two daughters, both their daugh
ters had married well off and therefore they really - stood out as a family in the particular area of - that we - where we lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Can you think of a family in a lower group and describe how they would live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, I can't think anyone - I can't thin
k - we were about all the same level round about - I should label them as honest working people - working class people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 So you wouldn't think one group felt itself superior to the rest?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, I wouldn't say so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Were some families then thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Well - some families were - like that I should say, but not just where I lived. But I've - I've a recollection of 'em - of an area just off the Ilkeston Road - where they were kind of - back to back houses
 and - mainly big families, and - some of those children, they didn't know what it was to have a pair of boots in the summer. You've seen 'em running about in their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 bare feet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  in the summer. Getting coal off }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 coal carts}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  from the road and all such things as that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Do you remember if there was a distinction of any kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Well, the only distinction that I can remember I remember my dad saying, he always used to say, he said, if you see two men, he says, one's got a big ha
mmer another's got a little 'un you can always bet the little - the man with the little hammer's getting the most money. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8282280\charrsid815340 Tht\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  the only distinction that I can think of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your mother and father have the same attitudes to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Well - I think my mother had some kind of - class distinction, she used to think that so and so was a lady, I think she'd been brought up that way while she was in service. In her young life, but - other than that I don't think she thought that anyo
ne near us were any better than us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What sort of group do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 She was just the ordinary working class group. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Was it possible at that time for move from one group to another, was there any social mobility?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I can't remember any instance of that. No. I can't remember any instance of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 In those days what do you remember - could you define a gentleman and a lady, not as you know them today but as you would then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well - my opinion, a lady was one who rode about in a carriage, that was the only thing that I could think about. The gentleman the same.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 A sort of superior class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Gentleman went to church in his - top hat and frock coat and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Do you remember seeing a policeman around when you were a child?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Oh yes. We always knew the policeman - he lived in the area, everybody knew him - and - I know - I can see him now, I knew his name and I knew where he lived and - he used to be a part of the community, h
e knew everybody. If anything went wrong he'd know where to go and - to - who to go and talk to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 So what did you think of him, you sort of respected him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Oh - respectful. Very respectful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 If you were naughty did your mother ever say, I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
No, I don't think I can ever remember - my mother - just one little instance of that, I do remember that - one time - I was - with some boys and been birdnesting, in Woolerton. And - the local policeman, he saw us, and we started to 
run and he - he called }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8282280\charrsid815340 my}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
 name, he said, it's no good you running, he says, I know you. Anyway, we stopped and he came up to us and - we used to put the birds}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8282280\charrsid815340 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  eggs we got in the peak of cap, we always wore caps, and we used to put the birds - the birds}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8282280\charrsid815340 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  e
ggs in the peak of the cap. And he said, where have you been? We said, we've been nowhere, we've been getting some dog daisies. So he said, well you've been birdnesting. Said, we haven't. And he hit me on the peak of me cap and broke all these eggs. He sa
ys, right, all right, go on. Anyways, when I saw my dad - on the Sunday he'd seen the policeman - and the police - he told me what had happened. And that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How do you think he treated people on the whole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well in - in those days as I say the policeman was - he was - you mean - I mean, you could have mentioned I mean along with the }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 vicar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  and the doctor, he could say that he was - one of the main members of the community.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 You think he was fair to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Oh definite - definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you ever see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. Only the agent. We never knew who belonged to the houses. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Can you remember having any feelings about the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, it never entered in,
 we just lived in a - just lived in the house. The agent used to come round for the money and that was it. For the rent money and that was it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 You remember that your parents had to struggle at times to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Can you remember what you thought about it then as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Well I thought it was just part of the general struggle, I thought everybody had to struggle like that. And that was the only thought that I ever gave to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work or on strike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Well the only thing was we used to have to get through the best we could. My mother - my mother had to resort to the pawn shop. I can remember we used to go with a jug up to the - up to this - chur
ch to fetch soup, pea soup, what the free issue of pea soup from the church and - from the parish church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How often would these sort of occurrences happen, how often was your father out of work or on strike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well - we never knew. I mean, the col
liers in those days were frequently on strike and when they did strike - when they did come out on strike it was generally a month or two, and I've got a recollection - I have got a recollection of going with my dad when he was out on strike and gathering
 nettles and we had boiled nettles for a meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
You were telling me about this soup from the parish church, was there any other form of relief that you got from either the Guardians or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, I can never remember any at all, I can never 
remember my mother applying for any relief. We just - just got through the best we could. She owed - we used to have the corner shop in those days, nobody went and paid cash, they always used to have a book, go to the corner shop - and then pay it off - i
f - if father was out of work these - some of these people were heroes, they - they must have had pounds owing to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 When you used to go and collect the soup from the local parish church how did they treat you, was the vicar there or who dished it out?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Well - generally church workers, probably vicar's wife, she used to - she used to have a big copper on, you know, in a - in a back place, a washing copper. And I think she used to go round the tradesmen and - scrounge meat and bones and vegetable
s and all that and - then issue the soup.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How did she treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 She treated us just like as if we were ordinary people, I can't see that she used to - ride a cock horse or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you have any special feelings about it, did you ever feel either resentful or glad?
