No, none at all, we used - I used to think - treat it just as everybody's doing the same thing and - we accepted then as just working class life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 When there was someone in the district who the people in the locali
ty disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it? There were areas in the country where people used to resort to playing what they called rough music, that was banging tin lids together, if they thought anyone was acting c
ontrary to the social behaviour that was accepted. Can you remember anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Yes. Definitely. I remember as a boy - if anybody in the district, especially we'll say - if a woman was suspected of - loose behaviour, if she was a married woman
 and suspected of loose behaviour, the women - neighbours and all that, they'd talk it over and that and - they'd go round to the house and they'd take a saucepan }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 and a saucepan lid}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  - and start }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7865441\charrsid815340 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
anging on the - saucepans. And - when these people - eventual
ly they used to practically drive them to leaving, which was no big obstacle in those days because there was always plenty of empty houses to - to go into, and when they left all the women used to gather round and they used to call it tinpanning them out.
 Tinpanning them out. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 And adultery would be the sort of behaviour that would provoke this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Adultery - mainly adultery. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11889103\charrsid815340 
People were very, very - keen on anything like that in those days.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Can you remember any effigy being made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, 
I can't remember anything like that. No. No. Well, to give you an instance of peoples' moral - thoughts and - on morals in those days, I can remember one occasion - when - we lived in a house next door to a - to an entry, and - the man who lived in the co
rresponding house on the next entry down the street one Saturday night, he'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11889103\charrsid815340 obviously}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
 been out and had a drink or two and he mistook his and he walked into our house. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11889103\charrsid815340 And I know my mother was very, very upset about it. You know, about the - me father wasn'
t in, and she was very - I was in the house at the time and I know my mother was very, very upset about it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
The thought that if any of the neighbours seen it or anything like that she'd think it was - the man was full of apologies and went out straight away but she was very upset about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Were you given lessons by one of your parents at home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Or a tutor or a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 So far as I can recollect I should be five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 When you first started school what time of the morning did you go and when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Nine o'clock 'til twelve. And then from twelve 'til four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 So you were going to afternoon school from the age of about five?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 From five, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What kind of school was it, was it a council school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 It was a council primary school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Was it mixed or just boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 I walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 How long would it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well I should say approximately about twenty minutes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did anybody go with you or did you go on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, well I can never remember anyone taking me. Only the first day I went to school when me mother took me the first day I went to school.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Where did you have your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 At home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What did you think of school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 
Well I - used to think it was just a matter of - passing the time on, at that time, and playing with other kiddies. People - kiddies that I knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 You didn't have any strong feelings about liking or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11889103\charrsid815340 disliking}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No. No. No strong feelings at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did you have any feelings about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 They were all - in the primary school they were all lady teachers. I think there were only three classes really in t
he school. Went up 'til about - to about seven years of age I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did the teachers emphasise certain things in life as being important, such as manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, I can't - I - they were really - did instruct you on manners but - and punctuality yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 No, I can't remember ever being - checked on ways of speaking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 When you did something wrong that the teacher disapproved of, what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well, in the primary school where }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8282280\charrsid815340 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8282280\charrsid815340 they\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340  probably go and make you s
tand in a corner. I - I can't remember any punishment in the primary school. Other than - just - just to - probably or report - said they'd report you to the headmistress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Were the girls treated the same as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Yes, as far as I know I can't remember any distinction between girls and boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 What sort of things that you did wrong would make the teacher stand you in the corner or threaten you with the headmistress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Well I can't really - pick any out. If you were late or anything like tha
t I should say, or - something like that, or if you made a noise in school or some - anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Not that I can remember. I can't remember - not at that time anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did they ask about what you did at school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 They used to ask what did you do at school, me mother did, what have you been doing today, and - all that business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did they visit the school and meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7889384 HF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Not that I can remember, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14102193 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15428707\charrsid815340 Did the other children in the school come from similar types of home to your own?
